data.title: Timbaland
data.meta_description: Read all about Timbaland with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

His influences include Prince and Rick James

Formed a short-lived group, Surrounded by Idiots, with future super-producer Pharrell Williams (of Neptunes fame) while in high school

Survived two brushes with death: a shooting that left him partially paralyzed for nine months and an auto accident that took the life of his passenger

Was given his "Timbaland" moniker by Jodeci's Devante Swing

Was high-school friends with Missy Elliott; produced many of her albums, including her debut, Supa Dupa Fly

In 2006, founded the record label Mosely Music Group

Has his own 5,000-square-foot studio in Virginia Beach and does most of his producing there
